{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-11125/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-11125"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:11:25"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["overhead"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Real mushroom is held up to drawing"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-11125","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-11125"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1/27282ae4-6afb-469b-bc3f-11b200fa00b8","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:26:10.979Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma compares her mushroom to the White Woolly Milk-Mushroom and the Bitter Boletus in M. C. Cooke’s <em>Edible and Poisonous Mushrooms: What to Eat and What to Avoid</em>. Cooke writes of the former: “Still more recently a correspondent in New Jersey writes distinctly that it is edible, for he has eaten it. These persons are competent judges of the true species, and quite as competent to pronounce on its properties, hence we conclude that it is not poisonous, although we class it with the poisonous species, because we are not prepared to recommend it without testing it” (120). Of the Bitter Boletus, he suggests, “The taste is bitter, and although disagreeable and unfit to be eaten, doubtless its poisonous properties have been exaggerated” (122).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11125/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:44.556962025316444,101.18143459915613,442.19409282700417,269.36708860759495"}}}]}]}]}